snippet.textDisplay: I knew that eventually some people here would be saying how Xiaoma should be avoiding Chinatown because of the corona virus.  But I'm sure he's safe.  Could you imagine the virus saying to him "No way I'm gonna mess with you, dude.  You're too cool! (to which Xiaoma respnds in Chinese "you're too kind, too kind!")  The virus replies "I'm actually a big fan of your videos" to which Xiaoma says "Wow.  Haishingba Haishingba (I appreciate that).  The virus then says "you know I've heard many of the Chinese people in China say they don't mind being quarantined inside their houses because now they have a lot of free time to watch your videos." Xiaoma replies "ooooooooh, no way, no way!" Before saying goodbye, the virus says "you know there's a limit to how far I could spread to people, but you could reach everyone in the world with your videos."  Xiaoma says "let me respond to your comment in Cantonese: siconga!  Bye,bye corona virus!"

snippet.textDisplay:
I was kinda shocked he said that, I consider it impolite to talk about someone in such a manner as though they wasn't there, especially since he knew that you guys can understand what he was saying, i'd of told him how I earn money I mean technically speaking your not jobless it's just the videos aren't as manual as giving multiple haircuts a day!
At any rate you inspire me Xiaoma (and I love that it means pony) but at any rate I am hoping to learn Japanese is the future as I a going to treatment for my condition soon, if it works I will be better and more energetic allowing me to pursue my goals and have energy to start learning languages without feeling drained all the time!

I hope one day I will be well enough to travel I plan to visit Tokyo and learn Japanese first!
Then if that goes well I plan to learn Mandarin and visit the Wudang Temple on the wudang mountains of Danjiangkou, Shiyan if i'm not too busy starting my business at the time I hope to learn Tai Chi there as I know a bit about the sects in the song dynasty but I am particularly interested in Taoism/Daoism


Reason being is the backstory of the head of the temple is that he was sick in a similar way I was of a weak constitution due to the harsh training and cold weather from the Buddhist temple he fell ill & had left to the Wudang temple very weak after they helped him recover


he began training there and grew strong and healthy to the point he became the master of the temple, if I can find the time to learn their ways I might finally be able to strengthen my core so I don't collapse and have a relapse again, western medicine often requires either daily medication or treatment for whatever it is that I have... so insight into eastern medicine may allow me to live a normal life without those treatments through meditation and the other techniques that help make ones body a temple!

I tried the basics of tai chi once at a Buddhist gym known as the temple gym here in UK once back when I was healthy but I got my attention grabbed by a games design course and I couldn't do both!

(my issue is people say pick a path in life but that isn't easy when theres so many for me to choose from life is full opportunities I wanna make sure I am choosing the path I am meant to be on before a final decision, but I am hopeful that I will be able to do more than one thing in my life)
